

**make sure thet the microcontroller u want to program, is supplied a clock and a power supply 


steps involved:

1: open arduino ide
2: from the tools menu select the relative aurdino board
3: select the relative port (from tools)
4: tools -> programmer select arduino as isp
5: from files -> examples burn the program ArduinoISP on to the board

6: unplug and make the following connections--

pin-arduino             microcontroller
13			19
12			18
11			17
10			1  (reset pin)


7: now select the kind of chip u want to burn in tools-> board
8a: select bootloader if u want to burn a boot loader
8b: if u want to upload a code just hold shift and uplaod the code (saya upload code using arduino as isp)